{
  "doc_id": "12485",
  "text": "The ascending aortic section of each animal was dissected, snap frozen in liquid nitrogen without any fixation and stored at À80 1C [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .Three different MALDI-MSI protocols were applied for the [CITATION_3] and metabolites [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Public libraries of MALDI-MSI data, MSiMass list database [CITATION_6] and MaTisse [CITATION_7] were used to assign identity of the most significantly altered protein molecular feature using a mass tolerance of 73 Da [CITATION_8] . Lipid molecular identification was performed by using exact mass measurements, peak peaking and spatial filtering combined with Lipidsmap database using a tolerance of r0.005 Da, as previously published [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] . For comparison between control and atherosclerotic tissue, a random selection of the whole spectra sets from these regions were then imported into ClinProTools 3.0 (Bruker Daltonik) where they underwent smoothing, baseline subtraction, mass spectral alignment and normalization. Mann-Whitney non-parametric tests were performed using GraphPad Prism software.",
